-- African Bank and Allied Technologies: South Africa Equity Market Preview
-- Franz Wild
-- 2010-07-06T22:01:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-06/african-bank-and-allied-technologies-south-africa-equity-market-preview.html

          
          
             The following is a list of companies
whose shares may have unusual price changes in South Africa.
Stock symbols are in parentheses after company names and prices
are from the last close.  
 South Africa’s  FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index  rose 541.2,
or 2.1 percent, to 26,723.87 in Johannesburg, its biggest gain
in three weeks.  
 African Bank Investments Ltd.  (ABL SJ): The bank holding
company, owner of South Africa’s largest provider of loans, said
it may sell as much as $1 billion of bonds to fund expansion.
The bank listed a so-called euro medium term note on the London
Stock Exchange to sell bonds in the U.K., Europe and Asia.
African Bank rose 58 cents, or 1.9 percent, to 31.55 rand.  
 Allied Technologies Ltd.  (ALT SJ): The electronics and
telecommunications holding company holds its annual general
meeting at 3 p.m. local time. Allied Technologies fell 42 cents,
or 0.7 percent, to 60.08 rand.  
